snippet: A stay-at-home dad in Kansas reveals how the lines have blurred between viral trolling and the business of politics.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to 2019, where it takes just 19 hours for a faked homemade video of Joe Biden to travel from the keyboard of a pseudonymous “memesmith” to the president of the United States.
abstract: A stay-at-home dad in Kansas reveals how the lines have blurred between viral trolling and the business of politics.

snippet: Unless he’s a glutton for punishment, he should not run. The times have changed more than he can grasp.
lead_paragraph: I watched Joe Biden at the Munich Security Conference earlier this year. “We will be back, we will be back,” he declared. He meant the United States after the moral abdication of the Trump years. He also meant himself, the president-in-waiting who would wait no longer to reach the Oval Office.

headline_main: Critics to Joe Biden: You’re Missing the Point

snippet: “I’m sorry I didn’t understand more,” Mr. Biden said about his hugs and kisses to women over the years. “I’m not sorry for any of my intentions.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Friday twice jokingly referred to complaints from several women that he had made them uncomfortable with his physical contact, and then offered a convoluted apology about their concerns and his behavior.

headline_main: Herman Cain, Brexit, Final Four: Your Friday Briefing

snippet: The president tweeted a doctored video mocking Mr. Biden for making unwanted physical contact with women, despite his own history of misconduct allegations.
lead_paragraph: Good Friday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
abstract: The president tweeted a doctored video mocking Mr. Biden for making unwanted physical contact with women, despite his own history of misconduct allegations.
headline_main: On Politics: Trump Goes After Biden

snippet: President Trump’s response seemed like a typical partisan jab, except for the fact that it was issued by a man who has been accused by more than a dozen women of sexual misconduct and assault.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, ignoring his own troubled history with women and bragging about sexual misconduct, went after Joseph R. Biden Jr. via Twitter on Thursday, posting a video that mocked the former vice president for his handsy approach to politicking.
abstract: President Trump’s response seemed like a typical partisan jab, except for the fact that it was issued by a man who has been accused by more than a dozen women of sexual misconduct and assault.
